0 artists, including Joseph Beuys (Berlin), Banksy (Israel-Palestine), and Frida Kahlo (Mexico-US). Through art and thus beyond art, we understand the flaws and shortcomings of supposedly well-oiled systems.With a preface by Élisabeth Vallet.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aArt History. 4aArt. 4aContemporary Art. 4aCultural History. 4aCultural Studies. 4aFine Arts. 4aGlobalization. 4aPolitics. 4aTheory of Art. 4aWall. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh  aArt History.  aCultural History.  aCultural Studies.  aFine Arts.  aPolitics.  aTheory of Art.1 aVallet, Élisabeth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2019 Part 2z978311076669108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2019z978311066277140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839447772zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839447772423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839447772/original  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066277-1  transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-